Configuration System API Map (Version 1.0 Freeze)

The Config System is the single source of static game data.

Configuration files contain no executable code.

Configuration files contain no gameplay flow.

Configuration files are read through ConfigLoader.

Managers never hardcode gameplay values.

Subsystems obtain configuration data from their corresponding configuration files.

Configuration files may reference resources but never load them directly.

